body_html: @bschreck: _input_producer is a fine solution for now, but it isn't part of the public API and will go away once we implement __all__. However, unless there's a reason we should probably remove the underscore and make it part of the public API.
body_text: @bschreck: _input_producer is a fine solution for now, but it isn't part of the public API and will go away once we implement __all__.  However, unless there's a reason we should probably remove the underscore and make it part of the public API.
body: @bschreck: `_input_producer` is a fine solution for now, but it isn't part of the public API and will go away once we implement `__all__`.  However, unless there's a reason we should probably remove the underscore and make it part of the public API.
